## ONE REFRAME FOR THE GENIE

The document is currently structured as *description of an architecture*. Consider reframing the introduction as *identification of a problem class* — there exist computations whose natural representation is relational and dynamic, and current architectures handle them poorly. The Phase Gradient Machine is then the proposed solution rather than the leading claim. That inversion makes the paper easier to evaluate and harder to dismiss.